---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '') + '/';
---

<Layout title="Home">
  <h1>Prime Period Theory Documentation</h1>
  <p>Welcome to the compiled documentation for Prime Period Theory (PPT). This site serves three primary purposes:</p>
  
  <div class="cards-container">
    <div class="card">
      <h2>1. A Perspective on Music</h2>
      <p>PPT offers a descriptive framework to analyse and conceptualise music, treating pitch, rhythm, and timbre as unified expressions of prime-generated periodicity.</p>
      <div class="section-links">
        <a href={`${base}topics`} class="action-link">Browse Curated Topics &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>2. Interactive Components <span class="badge">Coming Soon</span></h2>
      <p>Interactable music reference tools that bring PPT to life. These components are used throughout the documentation to demonstrate theoretical concepts, but are also independently usable by anyone who wants to integrate them into their own projects.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>3. OKF Knowledge Library</h2>
      <p>An agent and human-readable knowledge bundle structured in the Open Knowledge Format (OKF). Referencing standards like <a href="https://gist.github.com/karpathy/442a6bf555914893e9891c11519de94f" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Karpathy's LLMWiki</a> and <a href="https://cloud.google.com/blog/products/data-analytics/how-the-open-knowledge-format-can-improve-data-sharing" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Open Knowledge Format</a>, this semantic core is browsable as raw concepts or easily importable into any LLM conversation context.</p>
      
      <div class="prompt-box">
        <div class="prompt-header">
          <h4>Sample LLM Prompt</h4>
          <button id="copy-prompt-btn" class="copy-btn" aria-label="Copy prompt">Copy</button>
        </div>
        <code id="llm-prompt">Please read the Prime Period Theory knowledge bundle at https://ppt.midlifemuso.com/okf-bundle.txt. Reply with a short confirmation that you understand the core concepts, and wait for my next instructions.</code>
      </div>

      <div class="section-links">
        <a href={`${base}reference`} class="action-link">Browse Reference Library &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .cards-container {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
  .card {
    background: white;
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 6px -1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1), 0 2px 4px -1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
  .card h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: #1a202c;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .card p {
    color: #4a5568;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }
  .prompt-box {
    background: #f8fafc;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .prompt-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .prompt-header h4 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #64748b;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }
  .copy-btn {
    background: #e2e8f0;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: #4a5568;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    transition: background-color 0.2s, color 0.2s;
  }
  .copy-btn:hover {
    background: #cbd5e1;
    color: #1e293b;
  }
  .prompt-box code {
    background: none;
    padding: 0;
    color: #334155;
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Liberation Mono", "Courier New", monospace;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  .section-links {
    margin-top: auto;
  }
  .action-link {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--brand-primary);
    color: white !important;
    text-decoration: none;
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: background-color 0.2s;
  }
  .action-link:hover {
    background: var(--brand-accent);
  }
</style>

<script>
  const copyBtn = document.getElementById('copy-prompt-btn');
  const promptCode = document.getElementById('llm-prompt');
  
  if (copyBtn && promptCode) {
    copyBtn.addEventListener('click', async () => {
      try {
        await navigator.clipboard.writeText(promptCode.textContent || '');
        const originalText = copyBtn.innerText;
        copyBtn.innerText = 'Copied!';
        setTimeout(() => {
          copyBtn.innerText = originalText;
        }, 2000);
      } catch (err) {
        console.error('Failed to copy text: ', err);
      }
    });
  }
</script>
